<i>noun</i>: 합리화 [함니화], 추리 [추리], 추론 [추론], 논리 [놀리] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt>합리화 [함니화]</dt><br>
<dd>1. rationalization; reasoning</dd><br>
<dd>논리나 이치에 알맞게 함.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of making something in accordance with logic or reason.</dd><br>
<dd>2. rationalization; streamlining</dd><br>
<dd>낭비를 없애고 경제적이고 효율적으로 체제를 개선함.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of minimizing waste and improving a system to be more economical and efficient.</dd><br>
<dd>3. justification; making an excuse</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일을 한 뒤에, 그럴듯한 이유를 들어 그것을 옳은 일인 것처럼 꾸밈.</dd><br>
<dd>After doing a certain act, an act of coming up with a plausible reason for the act, to make it look right.</dd><br>
<dt>추리 [추리]</dt><br>
<dd>inference; reasoning</dd><br>
<dd>알고 있는 것을 바탕으로 알지 못하는 것을 미루어 생각함.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of guessing and judging something one does not know, based on what one knows.</dd><br>
<dt>추론 [추론]</dt><br>
<dd>inference; deduction; reasoning</dd><br>
<dd>미루어 생각하여 옳고 그름을 따짐.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of judging what is right or wrong after thinking about something, with a consideration of some factors.</dd><br>
<dt>논리 [놀리]</dt><br>
<dd>1. logic; reasoning</dd><br>
<dd>바르게 판단하고 이치에 맞게 생각하는 과정이나 원리.</dd><br>
<dd>The principle or process of judging and coming to understand something correctly.</dd><br>
<dd>2. logic</dd><br>
<dd>사물 속의 이치나 사물 간의 법칙적인 관계.</dd><br>
<dd>The logic of things, or the principle of relationship between two things.</dd><br>
<dd>3. logics</dd><br>
<dd>바르게 판단하고 인식하기 위한 생각의 형식과 방법 등을 연구하는 학문.</dd><br>
<dd>A field of study that studies the forms and methods of thinking in order to understand and reach correct conclusions.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>